---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { AUTHOR, CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../consts.js';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Speaking"
  description={`Invite ${AUTHOR} to speak at firesides, youth conferences, missionary preparation, and other events.`}
>
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 md:py-24">
      <p class="text-gold uppercase tracking-widest text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Speaking</p>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl text-navy mb-4">
        Reach the one
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-ink/85 mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        There is something that happens when I am in a room with youth or missionaries.
        I just find a tremendous amount of joy in it. Teaching, laughing, helping someone
        feel the Spirit. My whole goal is always to reach the one. If one person is touched
        by a testimony, a smile, or simply being noticed, then everything we do is worth it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-ink/85 mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        I am not out here booking a speaking tour. I have a day job and a book that just
        came out. But if you need someone who will show up early, stay late, and genuinely
        love being there, I would be honored to come.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-navy mb-6">Ideas for topics I could teach</h2>
      <p class="text-ink/80 mb-8 max-w-2xl">
        Each of these comes straight out of the book and the experiences behind it.
        Any of them can be tailored for youth, young adults, missionaries, parents, or
        ward and stake leaders.
      </p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-16">
        <div class="bg-white border border-navy/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy mb-2">Reluctant Disciples</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/80 m-0">
            Built around Lesson 2: you are sent where you are sent for a reason. For the
            person serving, dating, parenting, or just trying to hold on to faith and
            wondering whether they belong where the Lord has placed them. God does not
            waste anyone's willingness to try.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-navy/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy mb-2">Five Lessons of the Walk</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/80 m-0">
            An overview of all five lessons of the book: who you touch, where you are
            sent, keeping the Savior's life and ministry as the focus, the power of
            prayer and the Lord's love, and why the Savior's love (not the numbers) is
            the point.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-navy/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy mb-2">Reach the One</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/80 m-0">
            Built around Lesson 1: you never know who you will touch. Stories from
            Japan, from a small branch in Nobeoka, and from thirty years of watching
            quiet moments change lives. For youth, missionaries, and anyone who feels
            invisible.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-navy/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy mb-2">"How Do You Feel?"</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/80 m-0">
            Built around Lessons 3 and 5: keep the Savior at the center, and remember
            that the Spirit, not us, does the converting. A practical fireside on
            teaching, testifying, and helping people recognize the Savior's love when
            they feel it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-navy/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy mb-2">Pray Like He Hears You</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/80 m-0">
            Built around Lesson 4: do not underestimate the power of prayer or the
            Lord's love for you. For anyone who has been praying out of habit and
            wondering if it still counts.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-navy/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy mb-2">Missionary Preparation</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/80 m-0">
            For prospective missionaries and their parents. Honest stories from a
            reluctant missionary who learned the hard way what really matters in the
            field, and what does not.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-navy text-cream rounded-lg p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-cream mb-3">Send me a message</h2>
        <p class="text-cream/85 mb-6">
          The easiest way is the contact page, or you can email me directly at
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="text-gold underline">{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
          A short note about the date, location, audience, and what you're hoping for is
          plenty to start.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="inline-block rounded-md bg-gold text-navy font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 hover:bg-cream no-underline transition-colors"
        >
          Send a message
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
